The Vice Chancellor of Baze University, Abuja, Prof. Tahir Mamman, says the institution has adopted virtual learning mechanisms to ensure academic activities are not disrupted by the coronavirus pandemic. He told journalists that the university’s Senate made the decision after a meeting on Monday. “We feel the university has a strong IT system to ensure a form of continuity with the student in their programs in terms of their projects, continuous assessment even further lectures through the online distance learning facilities,” he said.  Baze varsity graduates 71 in maiden convocation Baze University graduates 64, honour late Adadevoh, Dasuki Towards an incorruptible cabinet for Buhari